# Observability — {{ project_name }}

How this project is observed (spec 08). Everything here is free-tier ($0). The goal:
**observable from birth** — structured logs queryable, golden signals dashboarded, errors
tied to releases, uptime public, SEV1s pushed to your phone.

## Signal map

| Signal | Producer | Destination | Status in this repo |
|---|---|---|---|
| Logs | `src/lib/log.ts` (frozen schema) | Workers Logs → Grafana Loki | **shipped** (structured JSONL); Loki export wired at setup |
| Metrics | OTel counters/histograms + Workers built-ins | Grafana Mimir | wire per project (OTLP secret below) |
| Traces | OTel auto-instrumentation | Grafana Tempo | wire per project (same OTLP pipeline) |
| Errors | `@sentry/cloudflare` | Sentry free tier | wire per project (DSN secret; `release` = version tag) |
| Uptime | Upptime repo `willzhu16/status` | GitHub Pages status page | add this app's URL to that repo |
| Cron heartbeat | `scheduled()` handler | healthchecks.io | **stub shipped** when `needs_scheduled_jobs`; point it at a check |

"Shipped" = already in the generated code. The rest are wired at first deploy via the
out-of-band steps below — metrics/traces/errors need accounts and secrets, so they can't be
baked into source.

## Health endpoint (shipped, frozen contract)

`GET /healthz` → `200 {"version":"<tag>"}` — no auth, no side effects, no binding fan-out.
It answers "is the Worker alive", not "is every binding happy" (binding health is a metric,
not an uptime probe). Consumed by Upptime, the release smoke check, and rollback
verification (spec 07). Do not add dependency checks to it.

## Logs

`src/lib/log.ts` emits one JSON object per line against the frozen log schema
(`handbook/log-schema.json`): `ts`, `level`, `event`, `projectVersion` always present;
`event` is the primary query key. Query in Loki by `event`. Never log secrets, PII, or the
bodies of auth/billing routes.

## Dashboard & alerts

- Dashboard: import `platform/observability/dashboard-project-health.json`. On import pick
  your Metrics (Mimir) and Logs (Loki) datasources and set `$project` to `{{ project_name }}`.
  Panels: request rate, error rate, p50/p95 latency, log volume, deploy annotations.
- Alerts: `platform/observability/alerts.yaml` — two rules mapping the frozen severities.
  **SEV1** (error rate >5% for 5 min) → ntfy push. **SEV3** (p95 >1s for 15 min) → batched
  email. Availability is covered by Upptime, which pushes downtime to the same ntfy topic.

## Backups & restore (spec 08 §4b)

Recovery point objective at solo scale: **24h**. If this project stores source-of-truth
data in D1, a nightly `wrangler d1 export` → the `backups-{{ project_name }}` R2 bucket keeps
30 daily + 6 monthly copies. R2 buckets holding user data get object versioning on; KV is
treated as rebuildable cache (say otherwise in `THREAT.md` if it isn't). **A backup that has
not been restored is a rumor** — the quarterly cadence restores the latest export into a
scratch database and runs the smoke test.

## Out-of-band setup (human, once per project)

1. Create a Grafana Cloud free account; provision OTLP + Loki tokens → `wrangler secret put`
   (`OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`, `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_HEADERS`, Loki push token) per the
   spec 06 secret-store pattern.
2. Create a Sentry project → `wrangler secret put SENTRY_DSN`.
3. Add this app's public URL to `willzhu16/status` (Upptime).
4. Import the dashboard (above); confirm `/healthz` shows green in Upptime.
5. Subscribe the ntfy app on your phone to the SEV1 topic.
